Spring.Persistence.Mapping.Attributes Classes

Classes
 NameDescription
AssociationAttribute

Represents type AssociationAttribute.

AutoGeneratedAttribute

Specifies that field or property value should be autoincremented.

ColumnAttribute

Is used to specify a mapped column for a persistent property or field.

DiscriminatorColumnAttribute

Is used to define the discriminator column for the SINGLE_TABLE and JOINED inheritance mapping strategies.

DiscriminatorValueAttribute

Is used to specify the value of the discriminator column for entities of the given type.

EntityAttribute

Specifies that the class is an entity.

ForeignJoinColumnAttribute

Represents type ForeignJoinColumnAttribute.

IdAttribute

Specifies the primary key property or field of an entity.

InheritenceAttribute

Defines the inheritance strategy to be used for an entity class hierarchy.

JoinColumnAttribute

Is used to specify a mapped column for joining an entity association.

ManyToOneAttribute

This annotation defines a single-valued association to another entity class that has many-to-one multiplicity.

ManyValuedAssociationAttribute

Represents type ManyValuedAssociationAttribute.

OneToManyAttribute

Defines a many-valued association with one-to-many multiplicity.

QueryAttribute

Represents query which should be used for given repository method.

SequenceAttribute

Specifies properties for databases which uses sequences instead of identities.

TableAttribute

This annotation specifies the primary table for the annotated entity.

TORMAttribute

Represents type TORMAttribute.

TransientAttribute

Represents type TransientAttribute.

UniqueConstraintAttribute

This annotation is used to specify that a unique constraint is to be included in the generated DDL for a primary or secondary table.

VersionAttribute

Is used to implement optimistic locking
